<h2>Government buys N1m rescue ship</h2>

<div><strong>Ocean</strong> going vessels that are shipwrecked inside the territorial waters of Nigeria would no longer have fears of being stranded in the high seas. This is because of a one-million naira multi-purpose rescue ship purchased by the Federal Government. The ship, Maris 1, which is expected in Lagos tomorrow is the first of its kind to be bought by the Nigerian government. Speaking in an interview with Sunday Punch, the Government Inspector of the Ships, Captain H.A Agate, said the ship which was completed sometime in May this year has been undergoing tests, It is a highly sophisticated shipping vessel that could be used for other purposes asides salvaging and rescue operations.</div>

</body>
